During retrieval, these cards are injected whole into the HotContext wrapped in a semantic containment box (`=== BEGIN INGESTED EVIDENCE ===`), loading the <pitfall> coordinates into the prompt prefix.

### 6.2 Real-Time Entropy Auditing in the Cognitive Mirror (Pillar II)

If the model encounters an ambiguous prompt or experiences statistical drift during inference, its next-token probability distribution becomes flat and high-entropy. 

The CognitiveMirror acts as an out-of-band sentinel, monitoring the entropy of next-token predictions. It calculates the Truncated Shannon Entropy (H(X)) across the sampling manifold of the active tokens:

```
H(X) = - sum_{i=1}^{k} [ P_(i,normalized) * log_2( P_(i,normalized) ) ]
```

If H(X) exceeds the strict mathematical threshold of 4.0 bits, the Chassis determines that the model has left its calibrated reasoning regime and entered a guessing state. 

The Chassis instantly raises a SovereignInterrupt, severs the stream, and rolls back execution before any unsafe token is committed.

### 6.3 Safe Teardown in the Ghost Ledger (Pillar III)

All tool proposals, shell commands, and file operations are quarantined inside an isolated workspace managed by the GhostLedger. 

If a safety check fails, the Ledger triggers an automatic, secure teardown: unlinking files using `O_NOFOLLOW` descriptors to prevent symlink hijacking, overwriting their raw bytes with null characters (`\x00`) in RAM, and flushing them to disk via os.fsync() before unlinking to eliminate forensic residues.

